entries.body:
It talks of a mountain, and the mountain is veiled to the party of Donatus.{fn:0} . . .

The holy Daniel saw a vision and wrote down what he saw, and he said that he had seen a stone hewn out of a mountain without hands. It is Christ, coming from the nation of the Jews, which was also a mountain, you see, because it has the kingdom. . . .

What is the mountain over which the heretics stumbled? Listen to Daniel again: And that stone grew and became a great mountain, such that it filled all the face of the earth.{fn:1} How right the psalm is to say to Christ the Lord as he rises again, Be exalted over the heavens, O God, and let your glory be over the whole earth.{fn:2} What is your glory over the whole earth? Over the whole earth your church, over the whole earth your bride. {fn:3}
